The Chronicle Sports Reporter
ZIMBABWE sevens rugby team manager Keegan Cooke has been chosen to be one of the adjudicators of the inaugural Rugby Africa Media and Photography Awards. The other Zimbabwean among the adjudicators is Rugby World Cup winner Tendai Mtawarira. The media awards are sponsored by the APO Group, a leading pan-African communications consulting and press release distribution service as well as Rugby Africa. The awards celebrate the best of African rugby sports journalism and photography and the jury will seek news and images that capture the passion for rugby in Africa and demonstrate the promotion and progression of the game across the continent. APO Group has been the main official sponsor of Rugby Africa since 2017. Entries for the awards will close on 17 July and results will be announced on 18 August. â€” @innocentskizoe